'From Squeak3.6beta of ''4 July 2003'' [latest update: #5331] on 12 July 2003 at 10:40:24 am'!"Change Set:		ImportsUndeclaredFix-nkDate:			12 July 2003Author:			Ned KonzCS 5296KCP68Imports caused an Undeclared reference to #default that came from Imports>>default. I assume that #default was meant to be a class instance variable; this code does this.The postscript of this change set deals with the Undeclared reference."!Object subclass: #Imports	instanceVariableNames: 'imports '	classVariableNames: ''	poolDictionaries: ''	category: 'System-Support'!Imports class	instanceVariableNames: 'default '!!Imports class methodsFor: 'instance creation' stamp: 'nk 7/12/2003 10:38'!default	"Answer my default instance, creating one if necessary."	"Imports default"	^default ifNil: [ default _ self new ]! !!Imports class methodsFor: 'instance creation' stamp: 'nk 7/12/2003 10:36'!default: anImports	"Set my default instance. Returns the old value if any."	| old |	old _ default.	default _ anImports.	^old! !"Postscript:The postscript of this change set deals with the Undeclared reference."Undeclared at: #default ifPresent: [ :def |	def class == Imports ifTrue: [ Undeclared removeKey: #default. Imports default: def ]].!